Reasoning: The paper deals with predicting future trajectories of objects, body joints, and frames in videos, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of stochastic neural network architectures and training schemes falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of these techniques to video prediction also falls under robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
